    "plan_content": "Here's the implementation plan I've laid out. Key findings from the code exploration:\n\n**Architecture:** `uv cache stats` fits exactly into the established pattern used by `uv cache size`. The codebase is highly modular — one file per command, all wired through `commands/mod.rs` and dispatched from `crates/uv/src/lib.rs`.\n\n**8 files to touch:**\n\n1. **`crates/uv-preview/src/lib.rs`** — Add `CacheStats = 1 << 28` to the `PreviewFeature` bitflags enum (plus `as_str()`, `FromStr`, and unit test entries)\n\n2. **`crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`** — Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` variant to `CacheCommand` and a `StatsArgs` struct with `--human` / `-H` (identical to `SizeArgs`)\n\n3. **`crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs`** *(new)* — The handler: iterates `CacheBucket::iter()` (10 buckets; `Python` is intentionally excluded from that iterator), measures each via `diskus::DiskUsage` (skipping missing dirs as 0), prints left-padded rows with a separator + Total at the end\n\n4. **`crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`** — Export + `mod` declaration\n\n5. **`crates/uv/src/lib.rs`** — Dispatch `CacheCommand::Stats(args)` to the new handler\n\n6. **`crates/uv-test/src/lib.rs`** — Add `cache_stats()` command helper and `with_filtered_cache_stats()` snapshot filter\n\n7. **`crates/uv/tests/it/main.rs`** — Register `mod cache_stats` under `test-python + test-pypi`\n\n8. **`crates/uv/tests/it/cache_stats.rs`** *(new)* — Three integration tests: empty cache, populated raw, populated human-readable\n\nOne thing to verify during implementation: `human_readable_bytes(0)` — the function takes the `log2()` of the byte count, so 0 will produce `-inf`, which Rust saturates to `0` when cast to `usize`, yielding the `\"B\"` unit and `0.0B` output. The test snapshots assume this; adjust if it differs.",
